  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\nI am trying to use a smart contract to publish data on it so that it can log back the data to the API, however I have noticed if the payload is lower than approximately less than 405KB it seems to be fine but anything over approximately over 405KB it fails. I am not sure if there is a maximum size in which a log can be e.g. 0.5MB. I am using JQ.Morgan's Quorum fork of Geth.\r\nCan I emit event logs more than 405KB approx? \r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth\r\nVersion: 1.8.18-stable\r\nQuorum Version: 2.3.0\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [63 62]\r\nNetwork Id: 1337\r\nGo Version: go1.9.3\r\nOperating System: linux\r\n\r\n\r\n````\r\norg.web3j.protocol.exceptions.ClientConnectionException: Invalid response received: 413; content length too large (526385>524288) at org.web3j.protocol.http.HttpService.performIO(HttpService.java:163) at org.web3j.protocol.Service.send(Service.java:34) at org.web3j.protocol.core.Request.send(Request.java:72) at org.web3j.quorum.tx.ClientTransactionManager.sendTransaction(ClientTransactionManager.java:83\r\n````\r\n",
